data.name: House at Pooh Corner by Kenny Loggins
data.description:
House at Pooh Corner was written by a teenage Kenny Loggins as he was getting ready to graduate from High School. Composed as an ode to lost innocence, as he prepared to leave his childhood behind, Kenny remembered the first book he’d ever read, A.A. Milne’s 1928 novel of short stories, “The House at Pooh Corner.”  

As Kenny identified Christopher Robin leaving the hundred acre wood with his own experience “House At Pooh Corner” was born.

data.name: Footloose by Kenny Loggins
data.description: Kenny Loggins and Kevin Bacon share the story behind the iconic movie soundtrack song Footloose. Released in 1984, Footloose spent three consecutive weeks at No. 1 on the US Billboard Hot 100 and is one of the most recognizable songs recorded by Loggins. Kick off the Sunday shoes and watch the story of this 80's classic unfold.
